window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Being a romance writer means drawing inspiration from many things, and when I met Dallin, I knew I had the perfect muse.</b></p> <p>He was everything women read about—tall, tattooed, and irresistibly delicious. Oh, did I mention successful too? He swept me off my feet and right into his bedroom where he awakened things in me, I had only ever written about.</p> <p>He was the bad boy who rode a motorcycle, and I was the good girl next door, yet together we were perfect.</p> <p>Or so I thought.</p> <p>When he invites his childhood best friends, Trey, and Parker, to stay with us, I realize right away there is more than meets the eye to their lifelong relationship.</p> <p>Dallin wants to share me. Amongst all three of them.</p> <p>But there's more than that because it turns out they like to share each other too.</p>"; 
